localised_description:
It is one thing to earn the Dark Prince's favour. It is another entirely to be ready to receive the alluring rewards of His gratitude in return. Open yourself up to His blessings, and indulge in the ecstasy of His gifts.

{{tr:hp_campaign_point_3_chaos_gifts}}

{{tr:hp_campaign_chaos_gifts_learn_more}}

Research, research, research! What experiments might pave the way to new diseases? What technologies might be used to expand your capacity for decay? These are questions you must answer, should you wish to receive the full extent of Grandfather Nurgle's deadly maladies!

{{tr:hp_campaign_point_3_chaos_gifts}}

{{tr:hp_campaign_chaos_gifts_learn_more}}

The gifts of the Blood God's favour are limited only by your capacity to receive them. Rid yourself of all but your wrath, and make room for every one of Khorne's blood-soaked blessings!

{{tr:hp_campaign_point_3_chaos_gifts}}

{{tr:hp_campaign_chaos_gifts_learn_more}}

An open mind is needed to better receive Tzeentch's endless knowledge. You must expand your capacity for understanding, in order to truly appreciate the Raven God's gifts.

{{tr:hp_campaign_point_3_chaos_gifts}}

{{tr:hp_campaign_chaos_gifts_learn_more}}

The north has long been bound to Chaos, and with much of its land under your thumb, it could finally become a true base of power. Build a Dark Fortress amidst the profane energies of Chaos here, as a symbol of your domination.

{{tr:hp_campaign_point_1_dark_fortress}}

{{tr:hp_campaign_dark_fortress_learn_more}}

Your army must thrive upon indulgence, and sweep the world up in the decadent delights of Slaanesh. Only then will the Dark Prince's supremacy be seen by all, a testament to his worldly dominion!

{{tr:hp_campaign_point_1_dark_authority}}

{{tr:hp_campaign_dark_authority_learn_more}}

It is time to concoct an unmatched tribute to the Lord of Pestilence. Spread your infections throughout your whole host, and unleash them as a walking plague upon the land!

{{tr:hp_campaign_point_1_dark_authority}}

{{tr:hp_campaign_dark_authority_learn_more}}

All must bow before the Blood God's throne, built atop the skulls of His enemies. Assemble a savage army of his most fervent warriors, who worship in war and bear the burning mark of His fury!

{{tr:hp_campaign_point_1_dark_authority}}

{{tr:hp_campaign_dark_authority_learn_more}}

By magic and blade, your army will change the fate of the world. Gather your followers by the thousand; each new servant of Tzeentch you acquire can only bolster the Wind-Lord's power!

{{tr:hp_campaign_point_1_dark_authority}}

{{tr:hp_campaign_dark_authority_learn_more}}

These wandering morsels fight for Chaos, but do not yet know the tantalising depths of its pleasures. Tempt them into submission, and prove once again that service to the Perfect Prince is most deliciously rewarded.

{{tr:hp_campaign_point_2_warbands}}

{{tr:hp_campaign_warbands_learn_more}}

It seems there are patients in need of a doctor to cure them of their fickle indecision. Perhaps an experiment is in order, to display the power of pestilence, and usher these peons into Grandfather Nurgle's rotten embrace?

{{tr:hp_campaign_point_2_warbands}}

{{tr:hp_campaign_warbands_learn_more}}

Only the most brutal warriors are worthy of bearing the Mark of Khorne. Bestow the honour upon the chosen, and let every drop of blood they spill pay homage to the Blood God!

{{tr:hp_campaign_point_2_warbands}}

{{tr:hp_campaign_warbands_learn_more}}

Every pitiful, twisted soul pleads for the blessings of change. Have them pledge their worthless lives to the Changer, and alter their fates forever!

{{tr:hp_campaign_point_2_warbands}}

{{tr:hp_campaign_warbands_learn_more}}

Some of the Heroes and Lords under your command have yet to succumb to the salacious delights Slaanesh offers. Persuade one such servant of the delicious power that awaits, once they pledge themselves to the Prince of Pleasure…

{{tr:hp_campaign_point_1_path_to_glory}}

{{tr:hp_campaign_path_to_glory_learn_more}}

Disease and decay must be spread wherever the opportunity arises. The most powerful servants of Chaos will surely vomit with glee, once infected by Nurgle's almighty pestilence!

{{tr:hp_campaign_point_1_path_to_glory}}

{{tr:hp_campaign_path_to_glory_learn_more}}

To be deemed worthy by the Sword-Maiden of the Blood God is an honour any Lord or Hero under your command would surely kill for. Choose only the mightiest of warriors, and let them burn with furious rage as they bear the Mark of Khorne!

{{tr:hp_campaign_point_1_path_to_glory}}

{{tr:hp_campaign_path_to_glory_learn_more}}

Every agent of Chaos ought to serve under Tzeentch's feathered wing. Open the mind of a Lord or Hero under your sway, and let the dark knowledge of the Great Conspirator fill them to the brim and fortify their power!

{{tr:hp_campaign_point_1_path_to_glory}}

{{tr:hp_campaign_path_to_glory_learn_more}}

Slaanesh offers a most enticing exchange; sacrifice the souls of your victims to sate his voracious appetite, and indulge in decadent reward!

{{tr:hp_campaign_point_1_chaos_gifts}}

{{tr:hp_campaign_chaos_gifts_learn_more}}

The Plague Lord awaits the souls of the dead and decaying corpses that litter the world in your wake. Send them his way, and receive his noxious gifts in exchange.

{{tr:hp_campaign_point_1_chaos_gifts}}

{{tr:hp_campaign_chaos_gifts_learn_more}}

Souls of the weak and unworthy deserve naught but to be devoured by the Lord of Murder. Sacrifice them in his honour, and claim the rewards of the Blood God's favour!

{{tr:hp_campaign_point_1_chaos_gifts}}

{{tr:hp_campaign_chaos_gifts_learn_more}}

Every soul signifies a life that could have been, where fate fluxes around every path not taken. Send them to Tzeentch, and as the Raven God is empowered, so will his faithful servants be also.

{{tr:hp_campaign_point_1_chaos_gifts}}

{{tr:hp_campaign_chaos_gifts_learn_more}}

As your devious influence spreads, your power grows all the more potent. Lavish it upon your willing servants, so that they may better serve Slaanesh!

{{tr:hp_campaign_point_3_warbands}}

{{tr:hp_campaign_warbands_learn_more}}

With just the right batch of toxic ingredients, what once was ordinary may become a decaying testament to the Plague Lord! The servants of Nurgle under your command are but one experiment away from fulfilling their pestilent potential.

{{tr:hp_campaign_point_3_warbands}}

{{tr:hp_campaign_warbands_learn_more}}

Victory after victory, your warriors prove their worth. Drenched in the blood of their fallen foes, they may rise up under your guidance, stronger than ever before!

{{tr:hp_campaign_point_3_warbands}}

{{tr:hp_campaign_warbands_learn_more}}

Change is inevitable, like an oncoming tide sweeping all into its churning waves. For their every victory, the soldiers under your command ought to be swept along in its current, and emerge transformed by Tzeentch's power.

{{tr:hp_campaign_point_3_warbands}}

{{tr:hp_campaign_warbands_learn_more}}

Norscan tribes bow before you, awaiting their chance to sow Ruin in your stead. Give these savage warriors a target, and watch them descend like rabid wolves in your name.

{{tr:hp_campaign_war_coordination_add_01}}

{{tr:hp_campaign_war_coordination_learn_more}}

[[i]]An endless array of armour and weapons must stream forth to provide the dark devices and works of occult engineering that arm the mighty hosts of the Dawi-Zharr. It is Hashut’s will![[/i]]

{{tr:hp_campaign_point_4_chd_economy}}

Learn more about Armaments [[url:script_link_campaign_chd_economy]]here[[/url]].

[[i]]When it comes to lucrative commodities traded over vast distances, an unprotected consignment is an attack waiting to happen. No chances can be taken for your most important goods – an armed convoy will be necessary.[[/i]]

{{tr:hp_campaign_point_1_military_convoys}}

Learn more about Military Convoys [[url:script_link_campaign_military_convoys]]here[[/url]].

[[i]]All life other than that of the Dawi-Zharr only has value as a resource – a commodity of muscle and sinew to be amassed, exploited and spent. Even now, the need for fresh Labour increases with time, the vast industries of your isolated empire ever hungering for more.[[/i]]

{{tr:hp_campaign_point_1_labour}}

Learn more about Labour [[url:script_link_campaign_labour]]here[[/url]].

[[i]]The greater works of the Hell-Forge, where the designs of your Daemonsmiths’ dark intellects spawn, is the bedrock upon which your power is founded. Establish your assembly lines of hellfire and blood![[/i]]

{{tr:hp_campaign_point_1_hellforge}}

Learn more about the Hell-Forge [[url:script_link_campaign_hellforge]]here[[/url]].

[[i]]The ringing of hammers echoes from your diabolic workshops, of Raw Materials being forged with arcane techniques to produce steelcraft of a quality that outmatches all other races’ craftsmanship. Ensure production meets demand.[[/i]]

{{tr:hp_campaign_point_5_chd_economy}}

Learn more about Armaments [[url:script_link_campaign_chd_economy]]here[[/url]].

[[i]]The desolation of a thousand years of Labour already fills your corner of the Dark Lands where industry tears at the earth, pock-marking the surface with the scars of enterprise. Continue these endeavours and reap the rewards![[/i]]

{{tr:hp_campaign_point_2_chd_economy}}

Learn more about Raw Materials [[url:script_link_campaign_chd_economy]]here[[/url]].

[[i]]The plundered riches of the earth must find their way onto your stockpiles, so to this end you must drill, dig and delve deep into the rock and filth in pursuit of the treasures that lie below. No landscape shall be spared![[/i]]

{{tr:hp_campaign_point_3_chd_economy}}

Learn more about Raw Materials [[url:script_link_campaign_chd_economy]]here[[/url]].

[[i]]The Tower of Zharr is a hustle and bustle of workshops, forges, Labourers and warriors, and where the powerful meet to exert their influence over them. To hold sway over its ancient districts is a path to power in itself, both for you and all Dawi-Zharr.[[/i]]

{{tr:hp_campaign_point_1_tower_of_zharr}}

Learn more about the Tower of Zharr [[url:script_link_campaign_tower_of_zharr]]here[[/url]].

Every wisp of Spirit Essence invokes a heady rush of power. With enough of its potent energy coarsing through your veins, the Hexes you uncover could be yours to command.

{{tr:hp_campaign_point_3_hexes}}

Learn more about Hexes [[url:script_link_campaign_hexes]]here[[/url]].

The tendrils of corruption have taken root deep within the land, befouling the very soil. Such evil must be eradicated if the natural order is ever to be restored; enact the [[i]]Purification Chant[[/i]], only then can we begin to cleanse the land of the scourge of Chaos.

{{tr:hp_campaign_point_2_hexes}}

Learn more about Hexes [[url:script_link_campaign_hexes]]here[[/url]].

The most potent spells are often created deep within the woods, amidst the whispers of strange incantations and the combination of unusual arcane artefacts. Each experiment brings new magic to life with which to guard the realms of nature.

{{tr:hp_campaign_point_1_witchs_hut}}

Learn more about the Witch's Hut [[url:script_link_campaign_witchs_hut]]here[[/url]].

The greatest deceptions will require you to be everywhere and nowhere all at once. Every foothold gained – whether by battle or infiltration – is a place to seed your schemes and expand the Trickster Cults.

{{tr:hp_campaign_point_1_trickster_cults}}

{{tr:wh3_dlc24_narrative_addendum_trickster_cults}}

It is always amusing when fools believe their defences will keep them safe – especially when your cultists have already taken root within their walls!

With a [[img:icon_hero]][[/img]]Trickster Cultist selected, right-click the desired target to show a range of Trickster Cult options.

{{tr:wh3_dlc24_narrative_addendum_trickster_cults}}

The vicious thralls of Chaos sate themselves on violence and destruction, ravaging lands held by the Dawi. The grudges incurred must be revenged, until the debt these savages owe in blood has been repaid in full.

{{tr:ui_text_replacements_localised_text_hp_campaign_point_1_grudges}}

{{tr:advice_info_texts_localised_text_war.camp.advice.grudges.info_003}}

With another slight avenged, a name may be struck from the Book of Grudges. Record this triumph in the Dammaz Kron, and bask in the reward of your fellow Dawi's gratitude.

{{tr:ui_text_replacements_localised_text_hp_campaign_point_4_grudges}}

{{tr:advice_info_texts_localised_text_war.camp.advice.grudges.info_003}}

Any oath sworn to kin and ally alike must be upheld. Strike out against those who would threaten the Forces of Order, for honour demands action in the fulfilment of your duty.

{{tr:ui_text_replacements_localised_text_hp_campaign_point_2_malakais_adventures}}

{{tr:ui_text_replacements_localised_text_hp_campaign_malakais_adventures_learn_more}}

The Spirit of Grungni is a wonder to behold, built by the sweat of your own brow. It is time the Thunderbarge is called into action, and launched headlong into the heat of battle!

{{tr:ui_text_replacements_localised_text_hp_campaign_point_4_spirit_of_grungni}}

Learn more about the Spirit of Grungni [[url:script_link_campaign_spirit_of_grungni]]here[[/url]].

For all the Spirit of Grungni's impeccable craftsmanship, the work on such a glorious feat of engineering is never truly complete. With some slight tinkering and reinforcement, the frame of the airship may yet still be improved.

{{tr:ui_text_replacements_localised_text_hp_campaign_point_2_spirit_of_grungni}}

Learn more about the Spirit of Grungni [[url:script_link_campaign_spirit_of_grungni]]here[[/url]].

Almighty Morr demands respect, wherever His cultists reside. A garden temple of tombs ought to be a worthy act of worship, with a tower at its heart, steeped in the magic of death.

{{tr:ui_text_replacements_localised_text_hp_campaign_point_1_gardens_of_morr}}

{{tr:ui_text_replacements_localised_text_hp_campaign_gardens_of_morr_learn_more}}

Wissenland prides itself in sparing no expense to thwart the Empire’s ever encroaching foes! The Elector Countess decrees full access to the Imperial Gunnery School’s advancements granted to you.

{{tr:ui_text_replacements_localised_text_hp_campaign_point_1_imperial_gunnery_school}}

{{tr:ui_text_replacements_localised_text_hp_campaign_imperial_gunnery_school_learn_more}}

The Imperial Gunnery School possesses many schematics meant to improve a weapon's firepower. It would be worth acquiring some, though the designs are as expensive as they are useful…

{{tr:ui_text_replacements_localised_text_hp_campaign_point_2_imperial_gunnery_school}}

{{tr:ui_text_replacements_localised_text_hp_campaign_imperial_gunnery_school_learn_more}}

As our foes grow stronger, so too must the Imperial cause. As the Emperor's authority is bound to his dominance over his rightful lands, it is every able servant's role to expand that authority at any cost.

{{tr:ui_text_replacements_localised_text_hp_campaign_point_1_empire_imperial_authority}}

Learn more about Imperial Authority [[url:script_link_campaign_imperial_authority]]here[[/url]].

The magic of the Amethyst Order is an art spurned by some, seen to blur the fragile line between life and death. Yet the dark power wielded by its practitioners is nothing to be scoffed at – perhaps your fellow Spiriters would serve you well?

{{tr:ui_text_replacements_localised_text_hp_campaign_point_4_imperial_gunnery_school}}

{{tr:ui_text_replacements_localised_text_hp_campaign_imperial_gunnery_school_learn_more}}

The Black Tower rises from the earth like a beacon, a looming symbol of arcane power. Morr bids you travel between these beacons of Shyish, to better study the dark secrets of Death Magic, within His welcoming embrace.

{{tr:ui_text_replacements_localised_text_hp_campaign_point_2_gardens_of_morr}}

{{tr:ui_text_replacements_localised_text_hp_campaign_gardens_of_morr_learn_more}}

The weak bow before the strong, and the strong bow before the even mightier still; such is the way of the Ruinous Powers. Thus, with a display of tremendous might, the Chieftains of Chaos would have no choice but to swear you their allegiance.

{{tr:ui_text_replacements_localised_text_hp_campaign_point_1_chieftains}}

{{tr:ui_text_replacements_localised_text_hp_campaign_chieftains_learn_more}}

As Chieftains swear their fealty, their followers too may bow before you, offering to cut a bloody path through your enemies. Swell your army with their blades, and amass a horde of legend.

{{tr:ui_text_replacements_localised_text_hp_campaign_point_4_chieftains}}

{{tr:ui_text_replacements_localised_text_hp_campaign_chieftains_learn_more}}

Every act of savage violence gladdens the hearts of Nurgle's faithful. Should you deign to slaughter their enemies on your bloody path of conquest, the Chieftains of filth and sickness will soon worship at your feet.

{{tr:ui_text_replacements_localised_text_hp_campaign_point_2_chieftains}}

{{tr:ui_text_replacements_localised_text_hp_campaign_chieftains_learn_more}}

